    • Method Detail

      • add

        public boolean add(E item)
        Adds the given item to this queue. This method may block until more space becomes available in this queue. If interrupted while blocked, this queue will be closed.
        Parameters:
        item - If null, it won't be added.
        Returns:
        true if the given item was added successfully.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If this queue is closed.

      • remove

        public E remove()
        Removes an item from this queue and returns it. This method may block until more items become available in this queue. If interrupted while blocked, this queue will be closed.
        Returns:
        null if there aren't any more items, which also implies that this queue is closed.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes this queue so that more items can't be added. Existing items in this queue won't be affected, and remove() may continue to return items.
